Program: Outlook
Title: 05/04/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00q88g3
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 6 Apr 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Somali doctor Hawa Abdi, whose 'extraordinary strength, courage and tenacity' have earned her a nomination for the 2012 Nobel Peace Prize. Jo Fidgen hears from her and her daughter Deqo Mohamed, who's just returned from Somalia. Then to Taiwan to meet Chang Chieh-Kuan, who's devoted his life to the traditional printing press. We also hear from Fred Rowe, a Londoner who turned his back on crime after making friends with singer Ian Dury. His story is told in Blitz Kids by Sean Longden. Show less